            <div class="features-row">
                <section>
                    <span class="icon major fa-refresh accent2"></span>
                    <h3>Sync with FieldWorks</h3>
                    <p>Collaborate on Language Forge then sync those changes back into Fieldworks Language Explorer.
                      Make further refinements in FieldWorks and then Send/Receive those back to Language Forge</p>
                </section>
                <section>
                    <span class="icon major fa-user accent3"></span>
                    <h3>User Roles and Permissions</h3>
                    <p>Assign each member of your project a role: observer, commenter, or collaborator. Customize what
                        other members see down to the field level.</p>
                </section>
            </div>
            <div class="features-row">
                <section>
                    <span class="icon major fa-cloud accent4"></span>
                    <h3>Access Anywhere</h3>
                    <p>Language Forge is built on web-technology, so it's available on Windows, Mac, Linux, iOS and
                        Android</p>
                </section>
                <section>
                    <span class="icon major fa-unlock-alt accent5"></span>
                    <h3>Engage Others while<br /> Retaining Control</h3>
                    <p>The commenting feature on Language Forge lets users comment on and suggest changes to individual
                        fields in the dictionary. As a manager you can review each comment and take action, resolve the
                        comment or mark it as TODO for later.</p>
                </section>
            </div>
        </section>

